Problem Statement: Customer Segmentation
Imagine you are a marketing manager for an e-commerce site. You have data on customers based on two metrics: Total Spend and Purchase Frequency. 
You want to group these customers into clusters so you can tailor your marketing strategies (e.g., a loyalty program for frequent spenders vs. discount codes for infrequent ones).
K-Means Clustering is an unsupervised learning algorithm that groups data points into $k$ clusters by minimizing the distance between the points and the center (centroid) of their assigned cluster.
The Python Implementation:
We use KMeans from scikit-learn. In this example, we will organize customers into 3 clusters.

Expected Output:
The algorithm iteratively moves the "center" of each group until the points are clustered as tightly as possible.
Console Output:
Customer Cluster Assignments:
Customer 1 [100 2] -> Cluster 1
Customer 4 [5000 20] -> Cluster 0
Customer 7 [2000 50] -> Cluster 2(...and so on for all points)

